BLACK SESAME SMOOTHIE
  DATE : 2014-08-14
  TAGS : black drink breakfast
  TIME : 20
  SERV : 1 serving
  DESC
    & This grey smoothie isn't only beautiful it's also very filling. Sweetened with dates if you're a fan of black sesame you'll love this drink.
  INST
    - Put 2 tbsp of black sesame seeds in a pan on medium heat, once they start to pop lower the heat. 
    - Stir and cook them until they get nice and crispy! 
    - Grind the sesame seeds into a rough powder using a mortar and pestle or a handblender. 
    - Blend with 1/2 a banana, 1/2 cup of soy milk, 1/2 cup of water, 1 tbsp of flax seeds, 1/2 cup of frozen blackberries and 3 chopped deglet noor dates.
  INGR
    Main
      Banana : 2 tbsp
      Black sesame seeds : 2 tbsp
      Soy Milk : 1/2 cup
      Flax seeds : 1 tbsp
      Blackberries : 1/2 cup
      Deglet noor dates : 3
      Water : 1/2 cup

CRANBERRY COOKIES
  DATE : 2014-08-15
  TAGS : dessert cookies
  TIME : 20
  SERV : 14 cookies
  DESC
    & These beauties are coloured naturally with beet root juice. These will look great on any table so try it out.
  INST
    - Preheat oven at 350F.
    - Mix 2 cups of all purpose flour, a 1/2 tsp salt and 2 tsp of baking powder in a bowl. Add in the handful of dried cranberries. 
    - In a separate bowl, whisk together a 1/2 cup of canola oil, 1 cup of brown sugar, 1 tsp of vanilla extract and a 1/4 cup of beet root juice.
    - Put the wet into your dry ingredients bowl and stir until everything is mixed together. 
    - Form little balls of pink dough with your hands and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
    - Bake for about 10 minutes, keep an eye on them to make sure they don't brown too much. 
    - Once the time is up take them out of the oven and let them rest for 5 minutes or so before transferring them to a cooling rack.
  INGR
    Main
      All purpose flour : 2 cups
      Baking powder : 2 tsp
      Sea salt : 1/2 tsp
      Dried cranberries : 1/4 cup
      Brown sugar : 1 cup
      Canola oil : 1/2 cup
      Vanilla extract : 1 tsp
      Beet root juice : 1/4 cup

SPINACH PAJEON
  DATE : 2014-08-19
  TAGS : korean dinner sidedish
  TIME : 15
  SERV : 1 pancake
  DESC
    & Korean-inspired dish scallion pancake coloured with spinach. This is a great way to add an extra portion of vegetables to pancakes plus the resulting colour looks great!
  INST
    * Pancake
    - Place a 1/2 cup of spinach and water in a blender and blend until smooth. Set aside.
    - In a bowl, whisk together 1/2 cup of spelt flour, 1 tsp sesame oil and pour the spinach water into it.
    - Heat a large pan with 1 tsp of sesame oil over medium heat.
    - Put the chopped scallions in the pan and pour the batter onto it. With a spatula press down on the pancake to flatten it out. Cook for 3-4 minutes until the sides come off the pan and the bottom is cooked. Then flip, cook for a bit and transfer to a plate.
    - Cut it into pieces to make it easier to dip into the sauce!
    * Sauce
    - Put the sauce ingredients together in a bowl and mix!
    - Serve as a dipping sauce for the spinach and scallion pancakes!
  INGR
    Main
      Spelt flour : 1/2 cup
      Water : 1/2 cup
      Sesame oil : 2 tsp
      Scallions : 1 bunch
      Spinach : 1/2 cup
    Sauce
      Soy sauce : 2 tbsp
      Rice vinegar : 1 tbsp
      Chili pepper flakes : 1 tsp
      Black sesame seeds : 1 tsp
      Maple syrup : 1 tsp
      Garlic : 1 clove

ZESTY TAMARIND MUFFIN IN A JAR
  DATE : 2014-08-22
  TAGS : dessert muffin
  TIME : 30
  SERV : 1 muffin
  DESC
    & A jar muffin is a perfect and simple way to satisfy a sudden craving for desert hard to go wrong with orange and tamarind. The reason this happened was because i didnt have a muffin pan or a ramekin. What I do have though is a ton of canning jars they make great molds and it worked really well for this recipe.
  INST
    - Preheat your oven to 350F. Grease a mason jar (or mug) with some oil.
    - In a small bowl mix 5 tbsp of all purpose flour, 1 tbsp ground flax seeds, a 1/8 tsp baking powder, a pinch of salt and 1/4 ts of cinnamon. Mix. 
    - In a separate bowl, mash 1/2 a banana with a fork, add a 1/4 tsp of vanilla extract, 2 tsp maple syrup, the juice of 1 orange and 1 1/2 tsp of tamarind paste (pits removed).
    - Combine wet and dry ingredients and mix well, then pour into mason jar.
    - Stick in the oven from 15-25 minutes, or stick a toothpick in. If it comes out dry it's ready!
    * Syrup
    - Heat 3 tbsp of water, 1 tsp of maple syrup and 1 tsp of tamarind paste and bring to a boil. Lower heat and let it sit for 5 minutes. 
    - Let the mixture cool down completely before pouring over the muffin, or stick in the fridge for a while. 
  INGR
    Main
      All purpose flour : 5 tbsp
      Flax seeds : 1 tbsp, ground
      Maple syrup : 2 tsp
      Baking powder : 2 tsp
      Sea salt : pinch
      Vanilla extract : 1/4 tsp
      Banana : 1/2
      Cinnamon : 1/4 tsp
      Tamarind paste : 1 1/2 tsp
      Orange : 2 tbsp juice, 1/2 tsp zest
    Syrup
      Tamarind paste : 1/2 tbsp
      Water : 1/2 tbsp
      Maple syrup : 1 tsp

HOUJICHA OVERNIGHT OATMEAL
  DATE : 2014-09-04
  TAGS : morning japanese
  TIME : 10
  SERV : 1 serving
  DESC
    & Start your morning off right with the nutty earthy flavour of houjicha oatmeal. If you're not familiar with houjicha visit a tea shop and ask for it. It's a japanese roasted tea that is often served with sweet and savoury dishes. It's a good low-caffeine alternative to most teas it adds just the right amount of flavour to oatmeal without overpowering it. Try it! 
    & Happy cooking!
    ? Rekka
  INST
    - Boil 1 cup of water, then infuse 1 1/2 tsp of houjicha leaves in a tea strainer. <small>You can leave it anywhere from 1-3min, it depends how strong you like your tea to be. The longer you brew houjicha the nuttier it'll taste. Remove the tea leaves and let it cool.</small>
    - Add a chopped banana as well as the tbsp of flax seeds, blend until smooth. 
    - Mix in 1/3 cup of oats, stir well and then put it in the fridge overnight. Enjoy for breakfast the next day! 
  INGR
    Main
      Oats : 1/3 cup
      Banana : 1
      Houjicha : 1 1/2 tsp
      Water : 1 cup
      Flax seeds : 1 tbsp 

