      Red onion : 1/4 sliced
      Garlic : 1 clove, minced
      Coconut oil : 1 tbsp
      Vegetable bouillon : 2 cups
      Soy milk : 2 cups
      Sea salt : 1/4 tsp
      Black pepper : pinch
      Red wine : 1/4 cup, Cabernet or Bordeaux
   
ROASTED CARROTS WITH BELUGA LENTILS
  DATE : 2014-10-25
  TAGS : dinner black
  TIME : 30
  SERV : 2 servings
  DESC
    & My oven has been working overtime these days i've been baking and roasting food almost everyday. Picked up a pack of heirloom carrots at atwater market last weekend threw them in the oven with a bit of oil and served them a bed of beluga lentils. All this topped with a delicious spicy peanut butter sauce.
    & Roasted carrots taste really different I find somewhat sweeter! I could have easily eaten all 8 carrots myself but alas i also need to feed Devine.
    % img/recipes/roasted.carrots.with.beluga.lentils.1.jpg
    & I like buying grains or flours in bulk I don't always get to buy huge quantities though because I can't bring a lot of it back. I don't own a car and walking long distances is out of the question. Since my bike accident i can't carry heavy loads for too long. Luckily i went to my parent's house on sunday they have a car and access to a terrific buy in bulk place. I bought a ton of black rice and some black beluga lentils! 
    & Not the cheapest kind you can get but certainly a wonderful addition to my black food pantry.
    & Worth mentioning that the idea to make a recipe with beluga lentils was inspired by Meike Peter's <a href=\"http://eatinmykitchen.meikepeters.com/beluga-lentil-salad-with-pear-blue-cheese-and-thyme/\">beluga lentil salad recipe</a>. 
    ? -Rekka
    
  INST
    * Carrots 
    - Preheat oven to 400F
    - Wash 8 heirloom carrots, do not peel them. Dry the carrots and then toss them with 1 tbsp of olive oil and 1 tsp of thyme.
    - Lay on a baking sheet and sprinkle with a dash of salt and black pepper. Bake for 25 minutes, make sure to flip the carrots halfway through.
    * Lentils
    - Wash 1/2 cup of beluga lentils. Put 375 ml of vegetable bouillon in a pot and add the lentils, bring to a boil.
    - Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 25 minutes. <small>Don't let them cook for too long, otherwise they'll get too mushy. If the lentils seem cooked but havent absorbed all of the water, just strain it out. </small>
    * Sauce
    - Mix 2 tbsp of sriracha, 2 tbsp of peanut butter, 1/4 cup soy sauce and 2 tbsp of rice vinegar in a small bowl. 
    * Combine
    - Set the beluga lentils on a plate with a bit of sauce and top with 4 roasted carrots! Makes two servings.
  INGR
    Carrots
      Heirloom carrots : 8
      Olive oil : 1 tbsp
      Thyme : 1 tsp
      Sea salt : 1 tsp
      Black pepper : pinch
    Lentils 
      Beluga lentils : 1/2 cup
      Vegetable bouillon : 375 ml
    Sauce
      Sriracha : 2 tbsp
      Soy sauce : 1/4 cup
      Peanut butter : 2 tbsp
      Rice vinegar : 2 tbsp

MATCHA PANCAKES
