    - Wet your hands and make small balls, this step should be done while they're still warm. Be careful not to burn yourself, feel free to use a spoon to scoop the mixture out. <small>You can also just pour the whole thing onto a pan and tap it down into a rectangle, flattening it with down with a spatula. It'll make bars instead of little balls, note that if you do make this shape instead you'll need to cut it into pieces early on.</small>
    - Lay them out on a baking pan and sprinkle fleur de sel over the candied peanut balls. Let cool and try not to devour them all at once.
