SIMPLE DOCTOR WHO CAKE
  DATE : 2015-01-06
  TAGS : dessert geek
  TIME : 60
  SERV : 12 servings
  DESC
    & I hardly ever bake cakes to be honest this was my first 'traditional cake'. By traditional I mean that it's a cake that has more than a single layer a filling etc. It's a proper cake. My sister's birthday was coming up and my parents really wanted make a themed cake for her... of what you ask?
    & Something old. Something new. Something borrowed...
    & Something blue!
    & You guessed correctly a tardis
    % img/recipes/simple.doctor.who.cake.1.jpg
    & They asked for a quote from their favourite bakery while they do great work it was a bit out of their price range. So my parents turned to me and my cake-baking adventure began.
    & My sister likes lemon cake so for sure it would need to be lemon-flavoured. That part didn't worry me. I didn't want to make a full tardis but i knew that i wanted the cake to be tardis blue. That colour is completely unnatural. Those royal blue raw blueberry pinterest cakes are complete bullshit. I had to go for food colouring I don't usually use those but in this case the tint was important. So i went ahead and bought Wilton's royal blue and violet colouring to get it be that specific shade. Just using royal blue would have made it go turquoise.
    & The cake noob that i am i didn't want to mess it up. Wanted my sister to have a half-decent cake. So I searched around and found a very awesome <a href=\"http://thegreenforks.com/vegan-birthday-cake/\">lemon cake recipe</a> by Laura i didn't want to mess it up. Wanted my sister to have a half-decent cake. So I searched around and found a very awesome <a href=\"http://thegreenforks.com/vegan-birthday-cake/\">lemon cake recipe</a> by Laura author of The Green forks. I adapted her recipe for this it turned out absolutely perfect. I only referenced her cake batter recipe for this cake though the tofu lemon curd filling was inspired by <a href=\"http://www.culinate.com/recipes/collections/Contributors/Zena+Chew/vegan_lemon_layer_cake\">Zena Chews</a>. Couldn't have done it without their recipes.
    % img/recipes/simple.doctor.who.cake.2.jpg
    & I didn't want to make a super sugary cake either so i decided to not add frosting. Opted for a powdered sugar dusted cake. Saw a lot of people making crazy tardis cakes made out of fondant. I personally HATE the taste of fondant while it helps to make beautiful cake art i just don't like it. Plus im not entirely sure i would have been able to pull off a decent fondant the tutorials i watched convinced me of that. Too high-level for me.
    & I wanted to make something clean something minimalistic. Then came the image of the tardis drifting through space. That image was simple. Evocative. So i cut out a tardis stencil
  INST
    * Lemon curd
    - Puree 2 cup of silken tofu, 2 tbsp of canola oil, 1 tbsp of lemon zest, 3 tbsp of maple syrup, 1/4 tsp of salt and 1/2 tsp of vanilla extract. Don't overmix.
    - Refrigerate for a few hours to give it time to thicken.
    * Tardis stencil
    - Print out your image in your prefered size, i just grabbed an image of the tardis that i found online.
    - With a fine cutting tool start cutting out the shape, I didn't take a photo that had lettering, the detail is just too fine and there is enough information that will make it obvious that it's a tardis. Be sure to cut out the windows, that detail is key.
    * Cake
    - Pre-heat oven at 350F
    - Grease two 8" cake pans, set aside.
    - In a bowl mix 2 1/4 cups of all purpose flour, 1 1/2 cups of sugar, 3/4 tsp of baking soda and 3/4 tsp of salt.
    - In a separate bowl, stir 1 1/2 cups of cold water with 3/4 cup of canola oil, 1 tbsp of vanilla extract, 3 tbsp of lemon juice and 1 tsp of lemon zest.
    - Combine wet ingredients into the dry ones, mix well. Stir in 1 tsp of royal blue food colouring with 1 drop of violet food colouring.
    - Pour cake batter into pans, at the 30 minute mark insert a toothpick in the center of the cake. If it comes out clean it's ready. Otherwise bake for an additional 5 minutes.
    - Let cool, slice part of the curved top off of one of the cakes to even it out. Brush with a generous serving of the tofu lemon curd, place second cake layer over it and press down gently.
    - Place tardis stencil over the cake 
    ? Make sure the top is completely dry, put some powdered sugar in a sifter or fine mesh strainer. Hold over the cake and gently shake it onto the cake until it's covered to your liking. Make sure to put enough around the stencil so the shapes comes out nicely.

  INGR
