FAUXMAGGIO POUTINE
  DATE : 2015-02-02
  TAGS : poutine dinner
  TIME : 40
  SERV : 2 servings
  DESC
    & This week is La Poutine Week! Montreal restaurants put their poutine skills to the test in an attempt to win the title of 'best poutine in the city'. Thought i would celebrate by making my own, The FAUX-maggio roasted beet poutine! Sweet potato fries with a blanket of faux-cheese and topped with roasted beets.
    % img/recipes/fauxmaggio.poutine.1.jpg
    & I have to admit that adding beets to a poutine was inspired by the one currently being served at <a href=\"http://lapoutineweek.com/montreal/the-poutines/chez-boris\">Chez Boris</a> theirs has more of a tex-mex feel with the beets mixed in with beans and chili peppers. I thought cubed beets looked beautiful atop a poutine!
    & The 'cheese' sauce is actually just inspired off a pasta sauce I make regularly at home. Because i don't eat dairy and am allergic to cashew cheese I usually make a nutritional yeast/mustard/turmeric/miso sauce. It mimics the look and taste of cheese. 
    & It would actually be just as delicious without the cauliflower bits but being a big cauliflower fan i just add it to everything. 
    ? -Rekka
  INST
    - Preheat oven to 400F .
    - Clean and cut 2 medium-sized sweet potatoes into strips. Toss strips with 1 tsp of olive oil, lay flat on baking sheet. Peel and cut 2 medium-sized beets into little cubes, toss with 1 tsp of olive oil, 1 tsp of ground cumin seeds along with a pinch of black pepper and sea salt. Put cubes onto another baking sheet.
    - Pop baking sheets in oven, bake fries for 30-40 minutes flipping them halfway through. Roast beet cubes for 20 minutes.
    - Put 1 tbsp of olive oil in a pan at medium heat, add 1 minced garlic clove and cook for a minute. Whisk in 1 tbsp of all purpose flour, stir continously to make sure there are no clumps.
    - Add 1 cup of water as well as 1 tsp of red miso, 1 tsp of dijon mustard, 2 tbsp of nutritional yeast and 1/2 tsp of turmeric powder. Stir to mix evenly. Add 1 cup of chopped cauliflower florets, bring to a boil and then lower heat. Let simmer for 15-20 minutes, or until the cauliflower has softened up.
    - Remove from heat, add 1 tsp of lemon juice, season with black pepper and sea salt and pour over fries. Top with roasted red beet cubes.
