      All purpose flour : 3 cups
      Bamboo charcoal powder : 1 tsp
      Sea salt : 1 tsp
      Olive oil : 1/4 cup
      Water : 3/4 cup, cold
    Filling 
      Black olives : 1 cup
      Arugula : few bunches 

BLACK SESAME ICE CREAM BARS
  DATE : 2015-05-04
  TAGS : dessert
  TIME : 120
  SERV : 4 large bars
  DESC
    & Black sesame ice cream bars because it's starting to get warmer in Montreal! And i want something sweet nutty refreshing and BLACK to eat!
    & Ok so it's not black. Grey is fine though grey is gorgeous. There should be more naturally grey foods.
    & So making crusts is always an ordeal for me most of the time i don't have the ingredients to make it. A lot of recipes call for graham crackers or dates while I do have dates i don't have an endless supply and i don't really want to use a whole cup of it (my wallet doesn't always allow it). Was wondering if there was something i could do with oats i always have a TON of steel cut oats on hand.
    & I looked up recipes for oat-based crusts and found this awesome one by <a href=\"http://www.oatmealwithafork.com/2014/11/14/5-ingredient-no-roll-pie-crust-gluten-free-nut-free/\">Lauren Goslin</a> from 'oatmeal with a fork'. Her recipe called for olive oil but I swapped it out for coconut oil. Coconut oil suits desserts perfectly :)! Assuming you like the taste of coconut because the flavour is pretty strong.
    % img/recipes/black.sesame.ice.cream.bars.2.jpg
    & As for the black sesame ice cream this is actually my 3rd attempt. First one was good made it with silken tofu and coconut milk. Didn't have any silken tofu left for this batch so gave bananas a go and it worked out great! Adds just the right amount of bulk.
    & Being able to make black sesame ice cream at home makes me happy. Now that Japan is so far away and that kombinis aren't 5 minutes away anymore. AH I miss the convenience of Kombinis.
    ? -Rekka
  INST
    * Crust
    - Preheat oven to 375F.
    - Put 1 1/2 cups of oat flour and 2 tbsp of sugar in a bowl. Mix well. Pour 1/4 cup of coconut oil and stir until the batter has a crumb-like texture. Stir in 4 tbsp of cold water to moisten it further. <small>you can make your own oat flour using steel cut oats by grinding them in a food processor or using an immersion blender.</small>
    - Spoon mixture into 4 mini loaf pans, flatten well with a fork. Bake for 10 minutes. Let cool. <small>I used mini kitchenaid silicone bread pans</small>
    * Ice cream
    - Heat 2/3 cups of black sesame seeds in a pan at medium heat, once they start to pop remove from heat and let cool. Transfer to a food processor and grind into a fine powder.
    - Put in a blender with 1 can of coconut milk, 4 tbsp of sugar and 1 banana. Pulse until smooth.
    - Put pans into a tray, separate batter evenly overtop of the oat crust into the 4 mini pans. <small>The reason i placed them on a tray is so i dont have to handle the silicone bread pans individually, since the mold is soft it means it can 'twist' and cause the batter to spill on the sides of the oat crust. Isn't a big deal but the presentation isn't as pretty if you can't see the two layers</small>
    - Put in the freezer for 3 hours or so. Pop out of the molds and store in another container or eat and enjoy! <small>After spending a long time in the fridge the ice cream part will get pretty hard, you should take it out of the freezer 10 minutes before eating it. It'll be softer and easier to eat that way</small>
    - One bar can serve 2 people! Just slice in two! Serve with fresh fruit.
  INGR
    Crust
      Oats : 1 1/2 cups, ground
      Sugar : 2 tbsp
      Coconut oil : 1/4 cup
      Water : 4 tbsp, cold 
    Ice cream
      Black sesame seeds : 2/3 cup
      Coconut milk : 1 can
      Sugar : 4 tbsp
      Banana : 1

LATKES WITH MAPLE MISO APPLE SAUCE 
  DATE : 2015-05-11
  TAGS : dinner lunch
  TIME : 30
  SERV : 4 latkes
  DESC
    & Make latkes with just two ingredients - Potatoes and onions! The toppings are the ones that will add all of the flavour the latkes I made are topped with balsamic marinated beets and maple-miso apple sauce. 
    & Latkes are fried potato pancakes seasoned and topped with various condiments like sour cream cheese or apples! I like fruits over savoury dishes so I opted to have apples on top.
    & If you don't have apple sauce at home but have a bunch of apples you can make your own. It doesn't take that much time! Just peel your apples and cut them into small cubes put in a pot and add water. Don't cover the apples make it so the waters sits just below the top layer. Mix in a splash lemon juice and bring to a boil. Lower to a simmer and cover let cook until the apples are softened. Remove from heat and mash with a fork!
    & There you have it! Unsweetened apple sauce. Did you know you could also make jelly with the apple peels and the cores? You can also make apple tea and apple cider vinegar check out <a href=\"http://www.littlehouseliving.com/uses-for-apple-peels.html\">Little house living</a> to find out how.
    & For the latkes i didn't want sweetened apple sauce but i did want to add an extra taste. I like mixing miso in everything so decided to give it a go. Tested a smaller portion in a separate bowl and DAYUM but i did want to add an extra taste. I like mixing miso in everything so decided to give it a go. Tested a smaller portion in a separate bowl and DAYUM it tastes good. It's even better with a bit of maple syrup the sweet helps to make the saltiness of the miso less overwhelming. Important to note that i used white miso less salty then red miso.
    & The inspiration for Latkes came from <a href=\"http://www.cookshideout.com/2014/03/potato-latkes-eggless-vegan-recipe-with.html\">Pavani</a> from Cook's hideout. Her recipe is completely egg-free although i didn't feel the need to add flour or the 'starch' to make it hold together.
    & I love simple solutions.
    ? -Rekka
  INST
    * Marinated beets
    - Preheat oven to 375F. Take 2 beets and cut off the stems, scrub them clean. Rub each lightly with olive oil and wrap them in foil. Roast for an hour or until fork-tender.
    - Let cool, cut into thin slices.
    - Mix 1 1/2 tbsp of olive oil, 1/2 tsp of dijon mustard, 1 tsp of thyme, 1 tbsp of balsamic vinegar as well as a pinch of sea salt and black pepper. Whisk together until well mixed. Add beets to the marinade and let sit for 2h (or overnight, best prepared ahead). Serve at roomt temperature. 
    * Latkes
    - Grate 2 potatoes as well as 1 yellow onion. Wrap in a cheese cloth and squeeze out excess liquid.
    - Put grated onion and potatoes in a bowl and season with sea salt and black pepper. Mix well.
    - Heat some oil at medium heat in a non-stick pan, when hot add 1/4 of the mixture and flatten with a spatula. Fry until bottom is golden and crispy. Flip and repeat. 
    * Apple sauce
    - Mix 1/4 cup of apple sauce with 1 1/2 tbsp of white miso and 1 tbsp of maple syrup. Stir to mix. 
    - Serve marinated beets over latkes with apple miso sauce with thinly sliced scallions
  INGR
    Marinated beets
