    % img/recipes/anise.bread.with.sweet.pear.sauce.2.jpg
    & I'm sorry i've neglected you for so long anise seeds. You're delicious and you smell so so nice. No hard feelings?We're good you and I right?
    & Right~
    & This recipe was inspired by a Pineapple and anise seed pudding chomeur recipe on <a href=\"http://willtravelforfood.com/2011/11/01/apollo-giovanni-recipe-pudding-chomeur/\">Will travel for food</a>! I ended up just making little cake breads instead of pudding. Making them egg-free worked out nicely too! My cake breads have a bit less sugar than the pinapple pudding chomeur.
    % img/recipes/anise.bread.with.sweet.pear.sauce.3.jpg
    & You guys should pay 'Will travel for food' a visit! It's a Montreal blog too :D how cool is that? More montreal cookies friends!
    ? -Rekka
